==Danish==
===Etymology===
Its origin stems from norse mythology and is found in [[w:Saxo Grammaticus|Saxo Grammaticus]] verses.
The famous verse ''[[w:Bjarkemål|Bjarkemål]]'' describes the exploits of Bjarke ([[w:Bödvar Bjarki|Bödvar Bjarki]]) and the other warriors of Rolf Krake's court.
===Proper noun===
'''Bjarke'''
# a male [[given name]] meaning ''bear'' or ''strong as a bear''
